        <p><strong>SLAC National Accelerator Laboratory</strong>, originally named <strong>Stanford Linear Accelerator Center</strong>, is a United States Department of Energy National Laboratory operated by Stanford University under the programmatic direction of the U.S. Department of Energy Office of Science and located in Menlo Park, California.</p>
        <p>The SLAC research program centres on experimental and theoretical research in elementary particle physics using electron beams and a broad program of research in atomic and solid-state physics, chemistry, biology, and medicine using synchrotron radiation.</p>
